      <abstract>
        <p>This article demonstrates a comprehensive pipeline for converting DOCX documents to JATS XML format with multiple output types. The pipeline generates XSD-compliant JATS XML, PMC-compliant XML with DOCTYPE, HTML with embedded media, and dual PDF outputs. We describe the methodology, implementation, and validation approaches used to ensure high-quality, standards-compliant outputs suitable for scholarly publishing.</p>
      </abstract>
