  <body>
    <sec id="sec1">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p>The conversion of Microsoft Word documents (DOCX) to JATS XML format is a critical requirement in modern scholarly publishing. This article presents a comprehensive pipeline that addresses this challenge by generating multiple output formats from a single source document.</p>
      <p>Our approach ensures compliance with both XSD schema validation and PMC (PubMed Central) guidelines, while also providing human-readable HTML and professionally formatted PDF outputs.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="sec2">
      <title>Methods</title>
      <sec id="sec2-1">
        <title>Pipeline Architecture</title>
        <p>The enhanced output pipeline consists of five main components:</p>
        <list list-type="order">
          <list-item>
            <p>JATS XML Generation (XSD-Compliant)</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>PMC-Compliant XML with DOCTYPE</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>HTML with Embedded Media</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>Direct DOCX to PDF Conversion</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>Standards-Compliant PDF from HTML/JATS</p>
          </list-item>
        </list>
      </sec>
      <sec id="sec2-2">
        <title>Validation Strategy</title>
        <p>All outputs undergo rigorous validation:</p>
        <list list-type="bullet">
          <list-item>
            <p>XSD schema validation for JATS XML</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>PMC Style Checker verification</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>W3C HTML validation</p>
          </list-item>
          <list-item>
            <p>Visual verification of PDFs</p>
          </list-item>
        </list>
      </sec>
    </sec>
